entity.Name: Contact

Description.description: Person with whom a business unit has a relationship, such as customer, supplier, and colleague.
The person’s date of birth as per the identification document.
Type of business associated with the contact.
Type of person’s relationship with the bank. This field must be set by the system through different processes such as customer enrollment, data migration, or complaints and opportunity capture.

The date from which charges must apply to the customer.
The person’s probability of churn (i.e. probability that the customer will leave the bank) as calculated in relevant back-end systems and analytical engines.
Latest Credit Score run against the customer
Debt Burden Ratio (%) of the person based on the person’s monthly income and liabilities.

Default account of the customer to be charged for different transaction fees and service charges that apply to the person based on service requests and transactions requested and carried out in branch
The bucket number in which the customer falls according to one's total overdue amount and past due days.
Total amount of payments that is overdue against the person’s existing loans and credit cards, for which one has become delinquent.
Value of the Delinquent Amount in base currency.
Flag indicating whether the person’s salary is transferred to this bank or not.
Flag indicating whether the person’s salary is transferred to this bank or not.
The company at which the person works.
The status of person’s employment such as salaried or self-employed.
The branch at which the customer was enrolled.
The date of expiry of the identification document provided by the person.

Indication of whether the person is Minor.
Indication of whether the person is Minor.
The person’s income per month.
Value of the Monthly Income in base currency.
Monthly Liabilities of the customer including loan payments and other monthly liabilities.
Value of the Monthly Liabilities in base currency.
The person’s place of birth as per the identification document.
The branch which the customer prefers to deal with.

The person’s status of residency in the country where he/she has a relationship with the bank.
Date from which the person has been resident of the country (if the person not a citizen and is a resident in the country where he/she has a relationship with the bank).
The total amount of Assets Under Management for the person with the bank as of now (total deposits and investments that the customer has with the bank).
Value of the Total Deposits in base currency.
The total amount of Risks Under Management for the person with the bank as of now (total outstanding amount of loans and credit cards).
Value of the Total Loans in base currency.
The expiry date of the person’s residence permit in the country where he/she has a relationship with the bank.
